ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: "MPCSI localizer: six axial, T1 weighted images, showing the placement of the multi-slice CSI acquisition."
"OVS images: 54 images in DICOM format, Axial acquisition, T1 weighted, showing the results of the MPCSI fat suppression routine for each coil element individually and combined for each slice."
"MPCSI P-file: GE file format containing the raw digitalization of the FID data for the MRS series, as well as scan-acquisition parameter header information and data structure for the file."

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: KKI MEGA-PRESS data file: Philips SDAT file format containing the raw digitalization of the FID data for the MRS series
KKI MEGA-PRESS header file: Philips SPAR file format containing the scan-acquisition parameter header information
KKI MEGA-PRESS water-reference data file: Philips SDAT file format containing the raw digitalization of the FID data for the water reference data
KKI MEGA-PRESS water-reference header file: Philips SPAR file format containing the scan-acquisition parameter header information.
Task condition of the trial measuremnet
MRS Voxel dimension in the sagittal direction
MRS Voxel dimension in the coronal direction
MRS Voxel dimension in the axial direction

Notes: hippocampus, anterior cingulate (ACC), insula, auditory cortex, or dfPFC

ElementDescription: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project (used for source IDs that change depending on timepoint/visit/etc.)
